From 5b09f1278f07b12f3b162a111826198f93a1f009 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 23:59:18 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: mt6397: add MT6351 core and interrupt support

MT6351 exposes four flat 16-bit interrupt enable and status banks. Its
status registers are write-one-to-clear, while the enable registers can
be written directly or through set/clear aliases. The PMIC reports
software ID 0x51 at register 0x202.

Generalize the legacy MT6397 interrupt controller by its configured bank
count, then add the four MT6351 banks and 64-source IRQ domain. Register
regulator, RTC, sound, and key MFD cells, including distinct power/home
press and release IRQ resources.

The register map and source enumeration are cross-checked against the
public Gemian MT6797 vendor source and live MT6351 E2 behavior.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
